Colombia Stock Movers: Bancolombia Rises; Chocolates Falls

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-03-16T20:42:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/colombia-stock-movers-bancolombia-textiles-fabricato-rise.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index declined 0.5 percent to 13,877.37, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.5 percent to 1,638.58.    Bancolombia SA (BCOLO)  , the nation’s biggest lender,
increased 0.5 percent to 27,600 pesos. The bank’s unit  Panama 
was rated new BBB- by  Fitch Ratings , with a stable outlook,
citing the support it would receive from its parent, according
to a Fitch report sent yesterday.    Grupo Nacional de Chocolates SA (CHOCOLA)  ,  Colombia ’s
largest food producer, fell 2.7 percent to 21,500 pesos, the
lowest price since July 13. Colombia, the second-largest
producer of arabica coffee after  Brazil , is being “seriously”
affected by climate change that hurts production, President  Juan
Manuel Santos  said in comments distributed by e-mail.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
